Creating Dax Measures 9

- Create  measure  

Per Month Per Port for Active Entry =

DIVIDE (
CALCULATE ( SUM ( BorderCrossing[Value] ) ),
CALCULATE (
COUNTA ( BorderCrossing[Value] ),
'BorderCrossing'[Value] <> 0
),
0
- Copy above DAX formula> right click on Table name > new measure >
- Paste and inter

Follow the same procedure and create all of following DAX formulas
Per day Per port Active Entry = ([Per

Month Per Port for Active   Entry]/30)

Per  Day Per Port = ROUND(BorderCrossing[Per day Per port Active Entry], 0)

Per day Per port Active Entry YoY% =

IF(

    ISFILTERED('BorderCrossing'[Date]),

    ERROR("Time intelligence quick measures can only be grouped or filtered by the Power BI-provided date hierarchy or primary date column."),

    VAR __PREV_YEAR =

        CALCULATE(

            [Per day Per port Active Entry],

            DATEADD('BorderCrossing'[Date].[Date], -1, YEAR)

        )

    RETURN

        DIVIDE([Per day Per port Active Entry] - __PREV_YEAR, __PREV_YEAR))

DIFFS YOY = SWITCH(TRUE(),[Per day

Per port Active Entry YoY%] <0, UNICHAR(9660),

 UNICHAR(9650))& ROUND([Per day Per port Active Entry YoY%],4)*100 & "%" 

Sum of Entries = SUM(BorderCrossing[Value])

Count all ports = count(BorderCrossing[Port

Name])

Actve Port Count = CALCULATE (COUNT ( BorderCrossing[Port Name] ),FILTER(BorderCrosing,BorderCrossing[Value] <> "0"))

For more detail about DAX  functions, go through this link,https://data-flair.training/blogs/power-bi-dax-basics/
